doc.ContractDescription: A LARGE FRACTION OF TOTAL ANTHROPOGENIC GREENHOUSE GAS EMISSIONS OCCUR IN REGIONS OF CONCENTRATED POPULATION, AND THE WORLD IS PROJECTED TO BECOME INCREASINGLY URBANIZED. ATMOSPHERIC GREENHOUSE GAS MONITORING SYSTEMS TARGETED ON URBAN ENVIRONMENTS CAN CAPTURE A GREAT DEAL OF INFORMATION ABOUT TOTAL EMISSIONS AND THE UNDERLYING PROCESSES THAT DRIVE THEM. HOWEVER, MEASUREMENT AND MODELING TECHNIQUES OF ATMOSPHERIC GREENHOUSE GASES IN URBAN ENVIRONMENTS ARE LARGELY UNTESTED. THE EMERGING AVAILABILITY OF MULTIPLE, INDEPENDENT, IN SITU AND REMOTE SENSING MEASUREMENT SYSTEMS FOR ATMOSPHERIC CARBON DIOXIDE IN THE NORTHEAST U.S. OFFERS AN UNPRECEDENTED OPPORTUNITY TO COMPARE MEASUREMENT METHODS AND THEIR UTILITY FOR CONSTRAINING URBAN GREENHOUSE GAS EMISSIONS. THE PROPOSED PROJECT WILL CONDUCT DETAILED EMPIRICAL COMPARISONS OF EXISTING AND DEVELOPING DATASETS OF IN SITU AND COLUMNINTEGRATED CARBON DIOXIDE CONCENTRATIONS FROM NETWORKS OF GROUND MEASUREMENT STATIONS AND FROM THE FORTHCOMING ORBITING CARBON OBSERVATORY-2 SATELLITE. THE PROJECT WILL THEN SIMULATE THE CARBON DIOXIDE CONCENTRATIONS FROM EACH MEASUREMENT SYSTEM USING A HIGH-RESOLUTION ATMOSPHERIC TRANSPORT MODEL AND EVALUATE THE CAPABILITY OF EACH MEASUREMENT SYSTEM, SEPARATELY AND TOGETHER, FOR CONSTRAINING URBAN FOSSIL-FUEL EMISSIONS WITH AN INVERSE MODELING FRAMEWORK. THE INTENSIVE AND DIVERSE SET OF CARBON DIOXIDE MEASUREMENTS AVAILABLE IN THIS REGION, IN ADDITION TO MULTIPLE ANCILLARY MEASUREMENTS OF ATMOSPHERIC STRUCTURE AND METEOROLOGICAL PARAMETERS, PROVIDES A UNIQUE OPPORTUNITY TO IDENTIFY UNCERTAINTIES IN INDIVIDUAL MEASUREMENT TECHNIQUES AND TO EVALUATE THE CAPABILITY OF EACH PLATFORM FOR DETECTING CARBON DIOXIDE ENHANCEMENTS IN URBAN ATMOSPHERES UNDER A VARIETY OF EMISSION SCENARIOS AND METEOROLOGICAL CONDITIONS. BROADLY, THE PROPOSED STUDY WILL CONTRIBUTE TO THE DEVELOPMENT AND DEMONSTRATION OF ATMOSPHEREBASED METHODS FOR MONITORING URBAN EMISSIONS, SERVE AS A CASE-STUDY FOR SYNTHESIZING MULTIPLE CARBON DIOXIDE MEASUREMENTS AT A RANGE OF SCALES, AND WILL HELP LINK THE NEW OCO-2 MEASUREMENTS TO THE OBSERVATIONAL APPROACHES NEED TO MEASURE THE INFLUENCE OF CONCENTRATED EMISSION SOURCES ON THE GLOBAL ATMOSPHERE.
